This paper proposes a spiking neural network model that encodes information in the relative timing of individual neuron spikes, which is a topic related to neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the supervised training of the network with backpropagation, which is a topic related to machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of synchronisation pulses and the alpha synaptic transfer function, which are topics related to control systems and signal processing, indicating that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category. The paper also discusses the performance of the network on classification tasks, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. Finally, the paper mentions the computational power of spiking networks with biological characteristics, which is a topic related to neuroscience and computational neuroscience, indicating that cs.NI (Neurons and Cognition) is another possible category.
